      { q: 'Sweeping (sampling) the joint space and plotting every tip reveals the:',
        o: ['Inverse Jacobian', 'Reachable workspace envelope', 'Control bandwidth', 'Settling time'], a: 1,
        e: 'The union of all sampled tips approximates the reachable set (workspace).' },
      { q: 'Redundancy is practically useful because it lets the arm:',
        o: ['Move faster than light', 'Reach a pose while avoiding obstacles', 'Eliminate all singularities', 'Ignore joint limits'], a: 1,
        e: 'Extra DOF let the elbow reconfigure (self-motion) to dodge obstacles at a fixed tip.' }
    ],
    '4': [
      { q: 'The unicycle / differential-drive model x_dot = v cos(theta), y_dot = v sin(theta), theta_dot = omega is:',
        o: ['Holonomic', 'Nonholonomic', 'Linear and decoupled', 'Static'], a: 1,
        e: 'It cannot translate sideways instantly; velocity is constrained to the heading.' },
      { q: 'Wrapping the heading error to [-pi, pi] is needed so the robot:',
        o: ['Moves faster', 'Turns the short way to the goal', 'Never stops', 'Ignores obstacles'], a: 1,
        e: 'Without wrapping it might spin the long way around (e.g. +350 deg vs -10 deg).' },
